1. ;; is the marker for one code block
2. let rec has to be explicit for recursive function
3. use let at the outter most place works as a global variable
4. need to use ref keyword to define something that is modifiable.
For ref variable, need to use ! to access the content of it. 
5. inside pattern maching can use keyword 'as' to name the thing that is evaluate and use it in the expression. 
6. use String.make 5 '*' to make repeated char strings
7. use open to include module 
